                            We are very keen to hear passengers' views on our proposals for local bus services
                            
                        </p>
                    </div>
                
            
            
            <p>
<p>A number of the proposals follow requests from the local borough councils of Hounslow and Ealing and are designed to serve the new Chiswick Office Park. </p>
<h3>Route 27</h3>
<p>It is proposed to extend route 27 from Turnham Green to continue along Chiswick High Road and terminate within Chiswick Office Park. </p>
<p>The route would no longer serve the bus stop in Heathfield Terrace. </p>
<h2>E10</h2>
<p>There are proposals to extend route E10 beyond Ealing Broadway to Chiswick Office Park. This will provide new links from Ealing to South Acton and Chiswick Office Park. </p>
<h2>H91</h2>
<p>It is proposed to alter route H91 to run along Chiswick High Road between Turnham Green and Chiswick Roundabout.</p>
<p>The changes would reduce journey time travelling through Chiswick and allow for easier interchange with Gunnersbury Station. </p>
<p>The route would no longer serve Town Hall Avenue, Heathfield Terrace, Wellesey Road and Oxford Road North; these roads would be served by route 440. </p>
<h2>440</h2>
<p>It is proposed to extend Route 440&nbsp;from Turnham Green to Power Road. The extension will provide new links from Chiswick Roundabout and Gunnersbury to Acton and Park Royal. </p>
<p>Peter Bradley, Head of Stakeholder Engagement, said: 'London's bus network is constantly under review, to ensure we continue to meet passenger needs. We are very keen to hear passengers' views on our proposals for local bus services.' </p>
<p>Further information about the proposals can be accessed through the <a href="/corporate/projectsandschemes/2033.aspx">bus consultations page</a>&nbsp;and also from London Buses Customer Services.&nbsp; The consultation will run until 15 August 2008.</p>
